HEADWORD: Cranage
<hw>Cran"age</hw> <pr>(kr⟦amac⟧n"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Crane</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The liberty of using a crane, as
for loading and unloading vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The money or price paid for the use of a
crane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cranberry</ent>⟦br⟧
